{Shortcode}: Detecting Radiation

The "Detecting Radiation" shortcode allows you to visualize the levels of radiation in your Minecraft world. This can be useful for tracking radiation sources, monitoring the effectiveness of shielding, or simply exploring radioactive areas.

To use this shortcode, add the following code to your config file:

```json
{
  "Shortcodes": {
    "Detecting Radiation": {
      "Category": "Physics",
      "Code": "radiationDetection"
    }
  }
}
```

This will add a new shortcode to your game called "Detecting Radiation." When used, it will display the current radiation level in the game, measured in Rads. The value will update in real-time as you move around the world.

Note: This shortcode requires the "Physics" mod to be installed and enabled.
